        <Bold>The Child Cancer Foundation Scholarship Fund aims to assist children aged 0 to 12 years with cancer, their siblings aged 0 to 12 years, or parents, achieve their personal education and developmental goals. Any activity that has the potential to educationally or developmentally benefit the applicant will be considered.</Bold>        
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="Black" FontSize="28" TextAlignment="Center" FontFamily="Gill Sans MT">
        The Scholarship sub-committee, which meets four times a year, receives and considers all applications. Allocations made depend on the funds available and are made according to the policy guidelines of the Child Cancer Foundation.
        <LineBreak></LineBreak>
        All application enquiries should be directed to your local Family Support Coordinator.
